The Central Bank issued 2.47 billionTaiwan dlrs worth of certificates of deposit (CDs), raising CDissues so far this year to 141.93 billion, a bank spokesmantold Reuters.    The new CDs, repayable from six months to one year, carryinterest rates ranging from 4.07 pct to five pct, he said.    The issues are intended to help curb the growth of the M-1bmoney supply, which has expanded as a result of large foreignexchange reserves.    The reserves hit a record 53 billion U.S. Dlrs this week. REUTER&#3;